&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PURPOSE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The Predictive Index—the talent optimization leader—is an award-winning best place to work (Inc., Glassdoor, Boston Business Journal, The Boston Globe).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Our mission is “Better work, Better world,” and we take great pride in PI’s power to supercharge workplace relationships and culture to achieve the unthinkable. We’re our own best case study! You’ll be working toward a mission that inspires you, and you’ll be surrounded by fun, smart, driven people day in and day out.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;There’s a reason more than 10,000 companies—including The LA Clippers, Hugo Boss, Nissan, Pendo, AstraZeneca, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;and Bosch—trust PI to help them hire top talent, design winning teams, and develop leaders at every level. Come discover how we empower our clients to solve their biggest challenges and make their business dreams come true.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em data-stringify-type=&quot;italic&quot;&gt;The Predictive Index is a place where people with diverse backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives collaborate on amazing, important work. We celebrate our differences, knowing that they are fundamental to our success as an organization. “Better Work, Better World,” starts here, in an organization where every member of the PI community is valued, respected, and welcome. We encourage people from underrepresented backgrounds to apply.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Product management on this team isn&#39;t coordination work. It&#39;s co-building the product with engineering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Product Manager to embed in a core PI2 product and engineering team and own the product surface at the intersection of behavioral science, enterprise workflow, and AI. You&#39;ll pair tightly with engineers moving fast, make decisions without waiting for permission, and use AI as a core instrument of your craft — not a side capability. You&#39;ll define what we build, why we build it, and how we know it worked.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But the role goes further. PI2 is evolving toward AI-delivered experiences that go well beyond a traditional UI; ambient, agentic, and API-first surfaces that meet users where they already work. You&#39;ll shape that evolution: defining the product model, designing for partners and integrations, and owning the outcomes that prove PI&#39;s value inside and outside the walls of our existing products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The AI landscape is moving fast. We don&#39;t expect you to arrive with every answer, but we expect you to be the kind of person who figures it out, stays curious, and learns faster than the pace of change. If you&#39;re a self-starter who thrives in ambiguity and gets energized by hard problems, this role was built for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the product strategy and roadmap for PI’s AI surface, Obi, and the AI-powered workflows built alongside it, with real accountability for response quality, user trust, and measurable outcomes across all of it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and maintain the evaluation framework that tells the team whether Obi and its adjacent workflows are working: rubrics, test cases, quality signals, and the instrumentation to track them over time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pair directly with engineers in tight delivery cycles, providing the clarity they need to move fast without waiting on meetings or approvals. Provide the deep details, including deep details on AI evals, prompt architecture,

